      "value": "Textual, physical, editorial, and digital layers are kept separate. Robert Thornton is a scribe and compiler of MS 91, not author of the romances. Halliwell is editor, selector, transcriber, and collator. Manuscript dates and locations do not become composition facts, and complete or partial image access is recorded at the exact facsimile layer.",
